5.title: Oxford colleges
5.text: Most colleges are build around an open  rectangular space like a courtyard which is often referred as a quad. The quad is one of the first spaces you enter when you walk throuth the porter's lodge and home to the original college buildings - but some of the modern colleges have recreated this. Quads are often named after famous former students. The quad is often a peacefull space in contrast to the hustle and bustle of the city outside.
